data.title: Player of the Week
data.meta_description: American Volleyball Scouting Report. Editor Bill Feldman. Recruiting service for colleges and universities in the USA.
data.text:
Last Week’s Action:

• In her American debut, Kattai powered Colby to four wins and emerged as the nation’s leading passer-hitter among junior college teams.

• Colby swept its four matches at the Midland College Kick-Off Classic in Texas, defeating Panola, Lee, New Mexico and host Midland.

• Kattai scored 64 kills at .299 efficiency, averaging 4.6 kills per set. As a receiver she committed only two errors while handling 69 serves.

• Colby is the defending champion of NJCAA Region VI. Last year’s team posted a 23-11 record and placed 12th at the NJCAA finals.

• Kattai has competed for Estonia’s national team at the women’s and junior levels. As a beach player she topped Estonia’s junior rankings.

• Kattai trained daily as a student-athlete at Audentes Sport School, a boarding school in Tallinn for athletes from throughout Estonia.
